10/08/2004
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Bombs exploded at two hotels in a tourist area in Istanbul early on Tuesday (10 August), killing two people and injuring 11.
Istanbul Police Chief Celalettin Cerrah told reporters that the incidents were terrorist attacks.
An unidentified caller warned police shortly before the first bomb went off.
Media reports said those killed were an Iranian man and a Turk.
Two Dutch citizens, two Chinese, a Ukrainian, a Turkmen and a Turk were injured.
In other news, two soldiers were killed and another one was wounded in southeast Turkey on Monday in what authorities described as an attack by Kurdish militants.
(AP, AFP, bTV, CNN, CNN Turk, Reuters - 10/08/04;
AFP - 09/08/04)
